defaultBSW Timber is a primary producer of sawn timber derived from sustainably grown and certified UK forests.
default 
default&#xa0;
default1.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFounded in 1848, BSW Timber is a family run business and the UK’s leading 
defaultsawmiller
default and one of the top 20 
defaultsawmillers
default in Europe. 
default&#xa0;
default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBSW employs 900
default people across 6 locations across Scotland, England and Wales as well as one plant in Latvia with a turnover over in excess of £180m. BSW Timber’s mills have a production capacity of over 1,000,000m3 of sawn timber per year and 
defaultwe
default produce over 30% of the UK’s softwood output. 
default&#xa0;
default1.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBSW have almost completed a five-year £
default70
defaultm investment programme, including erecting a new sawmill in Fort William and installing 26MWs of biomass capacity across three sites which utilises sawmills’ own lowest vale wood co-products for fuel. Our products are made from sawn timber and are mostly used for construction, pallet, packaging, DIY, fencing and gardens. Co-products are also used for paper, panel board and energy markets. We distribute timber products throughout the UK and export to the Middle East, China, South Korea and Japan. 
